Package: CausalCompetingRisks
Title: Separable Effects for Causal Inference with Competing Events
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Alex", "Mourer", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "MourerAlex@users.noreply.github.com")
    )
Description: Discrete-time pooled logistic regression estimators for total,
    direct, and separable effects in survival analysis with competing events.
    Implements the g-formula and inverse probability weighting (IPW) methods
    from Stensrud et al. (2020) <doi:10.1080/01621459.2020.1765783> and
    Stensrud et al. (2021) <doi:10.1007/s10985-021-09530-8>. Provides
    cumulative incidence estimation, causal contrasts (risk differences and
    risk ratios), bootstrap confidence intervals, and diagnostic tools for
    assessing the isolation conditions underlying separable effects.
